subject: p13979643
Findings: In comparison with the study of, there has been placement of a long intestinal tube that appears to extend well into the body of the stomach, then curl back on itself into the fundus with the tip pointed distally. Persistent opacification at the left base consistent with atelectasis and effusion. Engorgement of the pulmonary vessels is consistent with elevated pulmonary venous pressure. Left central catheter again extends to the lower portion of the SVC.
